##Wuhan Municipal Party Committee Secretary: 1499 critically ill patients were all hospitalized, all suspected patients tested or cleared on the 11th

Ma Guoqiang said that although the greatest efforts have been made to speed up the detection efficiency, but so far has not completely achieved the suspected patients test zero, the goal is to complete all suspected patients test zero by tomorrow.

”

Has the suspected patient been tested? Ma Guoqiang, deputy secretary of the CPC Hubei Provincial Committee and Secretary of the CPC Wuhan Municipal Committee, responded at a regular press conference on the prevention and control of COVID-19 infection in Hubei Province on February 10,2020, although the greatest efforts have been made to speed up the detection efficiency, but so far has not been fully achieved. "The goal is to have all suspected patients cleared by tomorrow. "

As of February 9,2400, there were 2618 new cases in Hubei Province, 29631 cases were reported and 871 cases died, the case fatality rate was 2.94% .

As of February 9, a total of 3,371 communities and villages had been surveyed, totaling 4.21 million households and 10.59 million people. The percentage of households surveyed reached 98.6 percent, and the percentage of people surveyed reached 99 percent.

According to Ma Guoqiang, after screening, as of February 8 there are still confirmed serious cases of 1499 people have not been hospitalized. As of noon on February 10, all 1499 critically ill patients had been admitted to hospital after efforts to open up beds for intensive care. In the aspect of treatment, Wuhan uses the mode of the shelter hospital to receive and treat the patients with mild diseases, and uses the three key hospitals in Wuhan —————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— Will adhere to the use of integrated Chinese and Western medicine for treatment.

"You may see that we have published figures that may also include suspected patients. Why? Because we add new suspected patients every day from sampling to testing, to the results back, there is a certain time frame. In addition, according to our testing protocol, a negative test can not be ruled out completely, so we have to wait a day for another negative test to be ruled out, while a positive diagnosis can be confirmed,"Ma said.

It is of concern that there are still patients'families reported the difficulties of admission to hospital, and how many patients have not been admitted to hospital? How to achieve the goal that patients should receive?

Ma Guoqiang said that through the street communities, currently there are still serious cases among suspected patients who have not been admitted to hospital for treatment. Through nearly two days of efforts, serious cases of suspected patients have been sent to non-designated hospitals for some simple treatment and isolation. At the same time will also speed up testing, confirmed with the continuous expansion of beds, I believe it will speed up admission and hospitalization.

In terms of clinical outcomes, what is the current cure rate? Zhang Dingyu, director of Wuhan's Golden Pond Hospital, said, "NCP is actually a self-limiting disease. The cure rate in our hospital is very high at present. At present, our hospital has admitted more than 1,500 patients. Most of the patients, including patients with severe illness, can be discharged smoothly after various oxygen therapy, symptomatic treatment and immunomodulatory treatment. There is no need for the public to panic."

Zhang Dingyu introduced that the current diagnosis and Treatment Program earlier there have been some progress. In terms of diagnosis, Hubei Province no longer emphasizes nucleic acid test as the sole diagnostic criterion; the light type is added to the clinical classification; the recommended medication for the confirmed patients is increased; the discharge criteria are standardized and the patients'clinical symptoms disappear, nUCLEIC ACID test was negative twice. Lung imaging showed obvious absorption of inflammation before discharge.

A netizen asks, Wuhan Protective Clothing still has gap everyday, whether can you recycle after killing protective clothing? Is there a Operability? Does the effect of protective clothing after sterilization affect protection?

Zhang dingyu said, on protective items, if it is a one-time protective clothing, the use of basic requirements is not repeated use. For example, the current use of disposable protective clothing, masks, shoe covers, boots, etc. can not be reused after disinfection. But some can be reused, such as goggles, rubber shoes and other protective products after disinfection, sterilization to achieve the appropriate disinfection norms can be recycled.

Referring to the current transfer of patients from mild to severe cases in Wuhan, and whether the medical resources of each designated medical institution are sufficient, Hong Xing Zhang, director of the Wuhan Health Commission, said: Referral generally to follow the principle of near referral, the city's designated medical institutions at present, we according to the case of admission to medical resources allocation.

"For patients with mild cases who have changed to severe cases due to changes in their condition, the referral mechanism will be activated quickly, and the medical treatment team of the municipal command will be notified by the medical institution where the patient is located, and then coordinated by a special transport class to refer the patient to the corresponding designated medical institution. Including the configuration of medical staff, protective materials, the current primary task of the designated medical institutions is to clearly diagnose the case of serious, critical and suspected cases of serious intensive treatment,"said Zhang Hongxing.

It is reported that with the advent of the national "Start Day" , Wuhan recently announced a plan to start stranded citizens outside the province to return to Han arrangements.

On how to implement the plan, Ma Guoqiang said it was very important to solve two problems: First, the native or permanent resident of Wuhan, who had moved to another place due to the Spring Festival, now hoped to return to Wuhan; and second, another group of people is working in Wuhan, because before the Spring Festival back to their hometown to go to Spring Festival, now need to return to Wuhan to work.

"At present, the prevention and control of the epidemic is in a state of stalemate. If pharmacies, supermarkets and hotels are to operate normally and meet the needs of daily life, they need to return to Wuhan. The concrete implementation is for the employers to put forward the demand, for the government to guarantee transportation, to ensure that they can smoothly and safely return to Wuhan, to put into the work,"Ma said.
